cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their communication protocols, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses stochastic routing of information messages, which involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and decoding. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a wireless sensor network, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes algorithms for selecting sensors, relays, and links in a distributed wireless sensor network, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms in a parameter estimation scenario, which can be viewed as a multimedia application.
